When we talk about performance, 1st thing we use is Indexes

Indexes
Why do we use indexes in Database? Indexes help in improving the performance
Eg: Book , with help of indexes we can go to any page refer to that pages context.
We take data in a particular table then we sort the data and store in some particular area.
From there if you wanted to search the data, as it sorted data, Searching is easier.

B tree Data Structure
One of the way, the Database stores its information in sorted order is B-Tree Structure. It improves the performance.
Traversing a tree from top to bottom is much more faster than reading every value.

Q)If indexes improve the performancethen I can index every column in table right?
A)Whatever query that I am writing, it will give good performnace. So I can create indexes on all columns.

Diadvantage of Indexes?
If you create an index, you are updating any row or if you deleting any row.
We need to update the actual table as well as you have to update the index.
For every update there will be 2writes that will be happening: one for table and one for index.
If there are 2 indexes then : 1 for table, 2nd for 1st index, 3rd for 2nd index - here need to write in 3 places.
This is where it impacts the performance.

Indexes will be improve the read performance of table, but impacts the write performance.

